This package implements Vigenere Cipher using Go.
This is my first shot at using Go so I may make improvements as I 'go' :)

NOTE: 

1. This program strips off all the special character and numerals from the plaintext before encrypting and changes the whole file to uppercase

2. The key must contain uppercase characters only

3. The folder also contains a sample plaintext file of 76 KBs

Command line syntax:


==================================================================================================
For Part 1
./vigenere-encrypt <alphabetical-key> <plaintextfile.txt> <ciphertext.txt>
This will automatically store all the ciphertext to the last file in the argument

./vigenere-decrypt <alphabetical-key> <ciphertext.txt> <recovered_plaintextfile.txt> 
This will automatically store all the recovered plaintext to the last file in the argument
===================================================================================================

===================================================================================================
For Part 2 and 3
./vigenere-keylength <ciphertextfile>
This will output the keylength and the actual key to the CLI
===================================================================================================
